page.title: 16Landscape
page.content:
The landscape of the block is downland with maritime associations.
The eastern 6sq.km is sea backed by a low shingle beach and low chalk cliffs angling away NNW from the shore to show where the sea once reached .Cliff heights are about 60 metres in the south of the block dropping away completely in three kilometres. Kingsdown village ,the major development sprawls down a fold in the downland which breaks through the cliffs and leads to the shore.Behind the beach,higher downland rolls down to the sea with folds or valleys leading roughly in a SW_NE direction. Heights in the SW corner of the block are approximately 65 metres falling away with increasing closeness to the sea. .
